WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.080
Hello everyone.

00:00:07.080 --> 00:00:09.870
I want to talk about why I built Sky for a Bridge

00:00:10.000 --> 00:00:14.200
and some of the technical challenges behind it.

00:00:14.310 --> 00:00:15.150
My name is Ryo.

00:00:15.190 --> 00:00:16.240
I'm from Japan.

00:00:16.240 --> 00:00:22.020
This is my first time speaking at an international conference, so

00:00:22.020 --> 00:00:23.910
I'm a bit nervous.

00:00:23.940 --> 00:00:28.980
But I'm very happy to be here and very grateful to

00:00:28.980 --> 00:00:30.860
Blue Sky for the support.

00:00:30.860 --> 00:00:36.940
So I work very hard to memorize the first part.

00:00:37.000 --> 00:00:40.980
But after this, I'll leave from my home.

00:00:40.980 --> 00:00:49.730
Please give me a - let me start.

00:00:49.920 --> 00:00:53.430
I learned this tool because of my personal experience.

00:00:53.430 --> 00:00:57.720
When Blue Sky first appeared, I was really excited.

00:00:57.720 --> 00:01:01.830
A new social network was starting and it was open.

00:01:01.870 --> 00:01:04.860
I thought that was very interesting, so I made an account

00:01:04.860 --> 00:01:04.860
early.

00:01:04.860 --> 00:01:04.860
But when I started using it, it felt a little lonely

00:01:04.860 --> 00:01:04.860
.

00:01:04.860 --> 00:01:04.860
Why?

00:01:04.860 --> 00:01:04.860
Because I did not know many people there.

00:01:04.860 --> 00:01:13.930
Making account was easy.

00:01:14.000 --> 00:01:14.000
But when I looked at my timeline, the people I usually

00:01:14.000 --> 00:01:14.000
follow were not there.

00:01:14.000 --> 00:01:22.020
My friends, my co-workers and people like to

00:01:22.020 --> 00:01:23.140
leave where are missing.

00:01:23.140 --> 00:01:32.270
Without

00:01:32.280 --> 00:01:32.280
familiar people, a social network can feel very bright.

00:01:32.280 --> 00:01:34.720
So I started doing this by hand.

00:01:34.740 --> 00:01:35.280
I think many people do the same.

00:01:35.280 --> 00:01:43.600
I open the blue sky search

00:01:43.600 --> 00:01:44.420
, type the name or username or someone I knew from X

00:01:44.420 --> 00:01:44.420
, and if I found them, I follow them.

00:01:44.420 --> 00:01:47.420
Then I searched for the next person and the next person.

00:01:47.420 --> 00:01:48.810
But if it was hard, it took a lot of time

00:01:48.810 --> 00:01:48.880
.

00:01:48.880 --> 00:01:51.420
It was trying, tiring.

00:01:51.420 --> 00:01:56.550
And some time, I still could not find the right person

00:01:56.730 --> 00:02:00.560
because the name was a little different or they use a different

00:02:00.560 --> 00:02:00.560
account.

00:02:00.560 --> 00:02:05.700
Then I thought, this is not just my problem.

00:02:05.700 --> 00:02:10.430
A lot of people moving to blue sky, we are doing

00:02:10.450 --> 00:02:12.680
the same thing.

00:02:12.700 --> 00:02:16.690
So I thought, it should be easier.

00:02:16.700 --> 00:02:20.620
But I thought, this is not just my problem.

00:02:20.620 --> 00:02:22.420
A lot of people moving to blue sky, we are doing

00:02:22.420 --> 00:02:23.220
the same thing.

00:02:23.220 --> 00:02:28.350
So I thought, it should be easier.

00:02:28.530 --> 00:02:32.300
That is why I build Sky for a bridge.

00:02:32.360 --> 00:02:38.410
This tool reads the people you follow on platform like X,

00:02:38.420 --> 00:02:45.100
looks for matching blue sky account and helps you follow them more

00:02:45.150 --> 00:02:46.180
easily.

00:02:46.180 --> 00:02:51.100
It helps with task people we are doing one by one by

00:02:51.100 --> 00:02:51.960
hand.

00:02:51.980 --> 00:02:56.120
First, I think it is easy to understand with the demo

00:02:56.170 --> 00:02:56.510
.

00:02:56.510 --> 00:02:59.120
So let me show you one.

00:02:59.120 --> 00:03:08.420
Open your profile

00:03:09.130 --> 00:03:11.040
on X.

00:03:11.040 --> 00:03:15.540
Click the Sky for a bridge extension.

00:03:15.540 --> 00:03:21.870
Enter your handle and log in.

00:03:21.880 --> 00:03:27.170
Open your following list.

00:03:27.180 --> 00:03:32.510
Click the extension again.

00:03:32.520 --> 00:03:35.220
Let's find Blue Sky users.

00:03:35.220 --> 00:03:39.240
Scanning your following list.

00:03:39.240 --> 00:03:46.180
Detecting Blue Sky users.

00:03:46.180 --> 00:03:51.470
OK, let's check results.

00:03:51.480 --> 00:03:55.220
About 500 users spawned.

00:03:55.220 --> 00:03:59.520
On the left, X users.

00:03:59.520 --> 00:04:03.440
On the right, much Blue Sky users.

00:04:03.440 --> 00:04:04.700
Oh, thank you.

00:04:04.700 --> 00:04:06.580
Let's follow one.

00:04:06.580 --> 00:04:10.570
Check it on Blue Sky.

00:04:10.580 --> 00:04:13.960
Follows successfully.

00:04:14.080 --> 00:04:14.550
Unfollowed.

00:04:14.580 --> 00:04:15.570
Unfollowed.

00:04:15.580 --> 00:04:16.770
Unfollowed.

00:04:16.780 --> 00:04:17.580
Unfollowed.

00:04:17.580 --> 00:04:22.710
Unfollowed successfully.

00:04:22.720 --> 00:04:27.220
Unfollowed successfully.

00:04:27.220 --> 00:04:34.940
And so that's how easy it is to follow users.

00:04:34.940 --> 00:04:35.930
Thank you.

00:04:35.940 --> 00:04:44.310
That's the end of the term

00:04:44.330 --> 00:04:45.450
.

00:04:45.580 --> 00:04:48.280
There was a useful future, too.

00:04:48.280 --> 00:04:52.170
So please try, if you're interested, you can use

00:04:52.170 --> 00:04:54.580
it on Chrome and Firefox.

00:04:54.580 --> 00:04:58.920
Next, I want to talk about two technical challenges.

00:04:58.920 --> 00:05:04.110
The first challenge was how to get the list of people of

00:05:04.140 --> 00:05:07.750
user followers.

00:05:07.760 --> 00:05:12.040
How do we get the list of people of user followers?

00:05:12.060 --> 00:05:18.610
At first, I thought I would use the API, but

00:05:18.720 --> 00:05:21.690
then X changed that a lot.

00:05:21.760 --> 00:05:28.930
As many of you remember, API access became very expensive for

00:05:28.990 --> 00:05:31.210
an individual developer like me.

00:05:31.220 --> 00:05:33.520
That was not realistic.

00:05:33.520 --> 00:05:36.220
So I changed my approach.

00:05:36.220 --> 00:05:41.250
Instead of using the API, I use the browser page.

00:05:41.260 --> 00:05:43.290
The user was looking at.

00:05:43.300 --> 00:05:47.200
The user was already logged in, and the falling list was

00:05:47.200 --> 00:05:48.900
already on the screen.

00:05:48.900 --> 00:05:51.200
So I viewed our browser extension.

00:05:51.200 --> 00:05:54.800
It reads the information directly from the DOM.

00:05:54.800 --> 00:05:58.320
That becomes a starting point, this tool.

00:05:58.320 --> 00:06:01.520
So it also gives me a clear structure.

00:06:01.520 --> 00:06:04.620
Only the first part depends on each platform.

00:06:04.620 --> 00:06:06.410
That part is reading the page.

00:06:06.420 --> 00:06:09.620
After that, the rest can be shared.

00:06:09.620 --> 00:06:12.860
Searching for blue sky accounts, showing the result, following

00:06:12.920 --> 00:06:15.500
account, and running search.

00:06:15.520 --> 00:06:21.150
And because of that, it became much easier to support my

00:06:21.150 --> 00:06:22.360
platform.

00:06:22.360 --> 00:06:27.960
Right now, X, Facebook, TikTok, Instagram, and

00:06:27.960 --> 00:06:29.280
threads.

00:06:29.280 --> 00:06:33.780
Of course, every platform has different DOM, so it is

00:06:33.780 --> 00:06:36.920
not easy.

00:06:36.920 --> 00:06:43.440
But this design made it much easier to add support for more

00:06:43.580 --> 00:06:45.020
platform.

00:06:45.020 --> 00:06:51.350
The second challenge was matching accuracy.

00:06:51.360 --> 00:06:54.100
How do you find the right person?

00:06:54.100 --> 00:06:55.570
This part was very important.

00:06:55.580 --> 00:07:01.460
People do not always use the same name across platforms.

00:07:01.480 --> 00:07:04.860
Some things the name is similar, and some time is complex

00:07:04.980 --> 00:07:06.020
difference.

00:07:06.020 --> 00:07:10.310
So find the right blue sky account is not easy.

00:07:10.320 --> 00:07:12.680
I use a few methods together.

00:07:12.680 --> 00:07:16.920
The basic one are the display name and account name.

00:07:16.930 --> 00:07:20.410
I also use the profile text to become some people put their

00:07:20.410 --> 00:07:23.660
blue sky account in the X profile.

00:07:23.660 --> 00:07:26.800
Recently, I added the avatar image matching.

00:07:26.800 --> 00:07:29.980
Many people use some profile image across platforms.

00:07:29.980 --> 00:07:32.400
So I use that as a hint.

00:07:32.400 --> 00:07:37.300
This works better than I expected.

00:07:37.300 --> 00:07:42.760
Over time, the project also became much bigger than I expected

00:07:42.760 --> 00:07:43.040
.

00:07:43.040 --> 00:07:46.280
Now, people from many countries use it, and it has

00:07:46.310 --> 00:07:50.660
been downloaded more than 520,000.

00:07:50.660 --> 00:07:52.150
Thank you.

00:07:52.160 --> 00:07:54.580
Thank you.

00:07:54.580 --> 00:07:58.380
When I started this project, I never thought so many people

00:07:58.420 --> 00:07:59.260
would use it.

00:07:59.260 --> 00:08:01.960
That is still surprising to me.

00:08:01.960 --> 00:08:05.950
And I was very happy when the official blue sky account shared

00:08:05.960 --> 00:08:10.800
it, and when users told me it helps them.

00:08:10.800 --> 00:08:13.700
What I learned is simple.

00:08:13.700 --> 00:08:17.760
When people move to new social network, making an account is

00:08:17.760 --> 00:08:18.280
easy.

00:08:18.280 --> 00:08:21.380
Finding people again is a hard part.

00:08:21.380 --> 00:08:25.510
And when we have to help with that, moving become much

00:08:25.510 --> 00:08:26.220
easier.

00:08:26.220 --> 00:08:29.600
So I want to leave you with one message.

00:08:29.660 --> 00:08:33.040
Open protocol needs migration, too.

00:08:33.040 --> 00:08:34.500
Open technology is important.

00:08:34.500 --> 00:08:42.140
But if we want people to really move, we also need

00:08:42.140 --> 00:08:43.580
bridges.

00:08:43.640 --> 00:08:47.160
Skyflower Bridge is one of those bridges, and I hope

00:08:47.180 --> 00:08:51.000
we will see many more in the future.

00:08:51.040 --> 00:08:57.880
Oh, thank you.

00:08:57.880 --> 00:08:58.880
Appendix.

00:08:58.880 --> 00:09:03.860
And once more appendix, there are also more attendees from

00:09:03.960 --> 00:09:04.760
Japan.

00:09:04.760 --> 00:09:11.250
Masaya is exploring the AT protocol ecosystem, and Nori

00:09:11.420 --> 00:09:14.370
aki Watanabe is the author of Swift AdProt

00:09:14.370 --> 00:09:14.700
.

00:09:14.700 --> 00:09:18.600
So please say hi if you see them at the conference.

00:09:18.600 --> 00:09:21.500
Thank you.
